{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:job.12",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 12,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 12",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 12 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.12.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:1",
      "text": "Then Job answered:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.12.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:2",
      "text": "“No doubt you are the people, and wisdom will die with you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.12.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:3",
      "text": "But I have understanding as well as you; I am not inferior to you. Who does not know such things as these?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.12.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:4",
      "text": "I am a laughingstock to my friends; I, who called upon God and he answered me, a just and blameless man, am a laughingstock.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.12.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:5",
      "text": "In the thought of one who is at ease there is contempt for misfortune; it is ready for those whose feet slip.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.12.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:6",
      "text": "The tents of robbers are at peace, and those who provoke God are secure, who bring their god in their hand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.12.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:7",
      "text": "“But ask the beasts, and they will teach you; the birds of the air, and they will tell you;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.12.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:8",
      "text": "or the plants of the earth, and they will teach you; and the fish of the sea will declare to you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.12.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:9",
      "text": "Who among all these does not know that the hand of the Lord has done this?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.12.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:10",
      "text": "In his hand is the life of every living thing and the breath of all mankind.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.12.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:11",
      "text": "Does not the ear try words as the palate tastes food?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.12.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:12",
      "text": "Wisdom is with the aged, and understanding in length of days.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.12.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:13",
      "text": "“With God are wisdom and might; he has counsel and understanding.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.12.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:14",
      "text": "If he tears down, none can rebuild; if he shuts a man in, none can open.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.12.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:15",
      "text": "If he withholds the waters, they dry up; if he sends them out, they overwhelm the land.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.12.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:16",
      "text": "With him are strength and wisdom; the deceived and the deceiver are his.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.12.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:17",
      "text": "He leads counselors away stripped, and judges he makes fools.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.12.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:18",
      "text": "He looses the bonds of kings, and binds a waistcloth on their loins.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.12.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:19",
      "text": "He leads priests away stripped, and overthrows the mighty.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.12.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:20",
      "text": "He deprives of speech those who are trusted, and takes away the discernment of the elders.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.12.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:21",
      "text": "He pours contempt on princes, and looses the belt of the strong.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.12.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:22",
      "text": "He uncovers the deeps out of darkness, and brings deep darkness to light.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.12.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:23",
      "text": "He makes nations great, and he destroys them: he enlarges nations, and leads them away.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.12.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:24",
      "text": "He takes away understanding from the chiefs of the people of the earth, and makes them wander in a pathless waste.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.12.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:25",
      "text": "They grope in the dark without light; and he makes them stagger like a drunken man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
